<section id="about" class="relative px-6 py-24 border-t border-white/5">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <p class="font-display text-sm tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-cyan-glow mb-4">About</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8">
      Four disciplines, one way of working
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-ink-200 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I'm an Information Technology graduate and machine learning engineer with hands-on
        experience gained through an internship at the Nigerian Army Cyber Warfare Command,
        where I supported cyber defence operations and network activity monitoring in a
        high-stakes, structured environment.
      </p>
      <p>
        My core work sits at the intersection of ML and full-stack engineering: I train and
        evaluate models — classification, feature engineering, handling imbalanced datasets —
        then take them the rest of the way, wrapping them in REST APIs, Flask or Django
        backends, and interfaces people can actually use, and deploying them to production.
      </p>
      <p>
        Design is not an afterthought bolted on at the end. I build brand identity, layout,
        and motion alongside the backend, because a model or a store is only as good as
        someone's ability to trust and use it. And outside of client work, I draw — ink,
        ballpoint, marker — which is where a lot of my eye for composition and detail comes
        from in the first place.
      </p>
    </div>

